CSS Grid is a powerful layout system that makes complex designs simple.
Basic GridCSSCollapseCopy.container { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }.container { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }Grid AreasCSSCollapseCopy.layout { display: grid; grid-template-areas: &#34;header header header&#34; &#34;sidebar main main&#34; &#34;footer footer footer&#34;; }.layout { display: grid; grid-template-areas: &#34;header header header&#34; &#34;sidebar main main&#34; &#34;footer footer footer&#34;; }Auto-fit vs Auto-fillUse auto-fit when you want items to stretch, auto-fill when you want to preserve track sizes.
CSSCollapseCopy.grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); }.grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); }
